# [自我评价]{.underline}

本人在生物/应用统计、数学与数据科学领域学术积淀深厚，毕业于多所知名高校，成绩优异，专注多维变量分析、时间序列分析等研究方向。实习经验丰富，涉足AI、通信、科研、医药、金融等多行业。在通信企业优化算法，提升模型准确率和数据处理效率；于科研项目处理海量数据、构建模型预测趋势；在医药领域运用多种分析方法助力药物研究决策。技术能力扎实，熟练掌握 R、Python 等多种编程语言与工具，具备多语言沟通能力。参与过教育、经济等领域项目，成果出色。校园工作中锻炼了组织协调和沟通能力。凭借这些能力与经验，有信心快速适应新工作，为团队贡献力量。

# [简历问答notes]{.underline}

### **“多样”解释为“复合优势”，把“跳跃”转化为“整合能力”。**

> 我认为我的多样性是我的复合优势，我的行业跃迁是我整合能力的体现。
>
> “您可能注意到，我的经历覆盖了数理统计学、生物统计、AI 算法、以及金融数据分析等多个领域。其实这并不是转行，而是我在不断构建‘数据驱动的跨学科能力体系’。
>
> 我始终认为未来的优秀人才不再局限于单一领域的专精，而是要能够在不同场景中把方法论迁移应用。
>
> 在生物医药行业尤其如此——统计建模、数据科学、临床设计、真实世界研究、AI 算法都在深度融合。\
> 所以我希望自己成为一名‘复合型人才’，既有严谨的统计思维，又能理解产业逻辑、技术实现和应用落地。\
> 这种背景让我能更快地把理论模型变成实际可用的解决方案，也能在跨部门协作中起到桥梁作用。”

💡**核心逻辑关键词**：\
“方法论迁移能力”“跨界融合”“统计为核心”“桥梁作用”“落地能力”。

------------------------------------------------------------------------

> “My background might look interdisciplinary — spanning statistics, public health, AI algorithms, and financial data — but that’s very intentional.\
> I see myself as building an integrated, cross-domain capability system where rigorous statistical reasoning can be applied to different problem spaces.\
> In today’s biopharma and data-driven industries, boundaries between statistics, data science, and application are becoming blurred.\
> I aim to be a *hybrid talent* — someone who can connect statistical modeling with real-world implementation, communicate across disciplines, and turn data into actionable insight.”

💡关键词：\
*cross-domain thinking*, *hybrid talent*, *statistical rigor with practical insight*, *interdisciplinary problem-solving*。

------------------------------------------------------------------------

> “我希望成为那种‘懂算法、懂业务、懂落地’的复合型人才，用统计学的逻辑去连接技术与决策。”

或英文：

> “I aspire to be a hybrid professional who bridges analytics, technology, and business decision-making through statistical thinking.”

### [自我介绍]{.underline}

> 各位面试官大家好，我叫Johnny，目前就读于哈佛大学生物统计专业。在哥伦比亚大学获得了了应用统计硕士；本科呢，毕业于多伦多大学数学与统计学双学位，
>
> 我目前的研究方向主要集中在**统计建模、数据科学与生物信息学的交叉领域**。之前的研究领域是多为变量分析和时间序列。目前我在哈佛多个科研机构lab担任RA。在 Dana-Farber 癌症研究所，我参与由 R 语言共同创始人指导的 Epiconnector 项目，搭建可重复的科研计算环境，用于提升生物统计分析的可复现性。然后即将在另一个哈佛下属科研机构Sofer's Lab参与基于 HCHS/SOL 队列的多组学数据分析项目，搭建 Snakemake 与 Bioconductor 驱动的自动化分析流程，研究基因表达与睡眠表型之间的关系。
>
> 我之前在中国移动研究院担任过全职的 AI 算法工程师岗位。主要负责**表格数据理解和时间序列建模算法的开发与优化**，包括大语言模型的微调以及原油价格预测模型的构建。
>
> 此外，在国药集团的实习让我熟悉了真实世界证据（RWE）研究和临床数据的统计分析方法，如 Cox 模型、生存分析与可视化报表；在中金的研究经历则训练了我严谨的数据建模思维和宏观逻辑。
>
> 我认为这些经历虽然跨领域，但核心都是围绕“如何让数据更有价值”。从 AI 算法到生物统计，从编程到临床研究，我始终致力于将技术方法转化为可落地的分析体系。这也正是我认为自己与恒瑞匹配的地方——我希望能在恒瑞这样的创新型医药平台上，将自己的统计建模与编程能力融入临床研发流程中，成为一名真正的**复合型生物统计人才**。
>
> Here’s a polished and natural English version of your self-introduction, tailored for an interview setting like Lilly’s Marketing Academy — fluent, professional, and confident while keeping your academic and technical background clear:
>
> ------------------------------------------------------------------------
>
> **English Version:**
>
> Dear interviews, pleasure to meet you all, my name is Putian Zhao and I also go by Johnny; so feel free to call me whichever the one you want. I’m currently a grad student at Harvard University majoring biostatistics. I previously earned my Master’s in Applied Statistics from Columbia University, and my undergraduate degree was a double major in Mathematics and Statistics from the University of Toronto.
>
> My current research interests lie at the intersection of statistical modeling, data science, algotrithms and genetics. Earlier, I focused on multivariate analysis and time series analysis. Here at Harvard, I’m now working as a Research Assistant in several labs. At the Dana-Farber Cancer Institute, I’m part of the *Epiconnector Project* led by one of the co-founders of R, Dr. Gentleman, who is also my director, where we build reproducible research environments to enhance transparency and replicability in biostatistical analysis. I’ll also soon be joining Sofer’s Lab at Beth Israel Deaconess Medical Center, where we’re developing automated pipelines using Snakemake and Bioconductor to study associations between gene expression and sleep phenotypes based on the HCHS/SOL cohort.
>
> Previously, I worked full-time as an AI Algorithm Engineer at China Mobile Research Institute, focusing on table understanding and time series modeling — including fine-tuning large language models and developing a crude oil price forecasting system.
>
> In addition, my internship at Sinopharm introduced me to real-world evidence (RWE) studies and clinical data analytics, applying methods such as Cox models, survival analysis, and interactive dashboards. My research experience at CICC trained me to think critically about data modeling and maintain a rigorous, analytical mindset toward macro-level insights.
>
> Although my experiences span multiple fields, they all revolve around one core goal — *making data more valuable*. From AI algorithms to biostatistics, from programming to clinical research, I’ve always aimed to translate technical methods into actionable analytical frameworks. That’s also why I believe I’m a strong fit for Lilly — an innovative and data-driven company where I can integrate my modeling and programming expertise into healthcare and clinical development, and grow into a well-rounded biostatistics professional.

------------------------------------------------------------------------

